command line youtube video downloader and player

dependencies: wget, mplayer, sh, grep, sed, echo

put the scripts somewhere under $PATH or add shell aliases eg. in ~/.bashrc
	alias yget = ~/path/to/yget
	alias yplay = ~/path/to/yplay

usgage:
	yget url [prefix]
	default prefix is "y" and "y[number]_" when it's a playlist

usage examples:
	yplay 'youtube.com/watch?v=abcdefghijk&foo=123&bar=456'
	yget http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=abcdefghijk
	yget youtube.co.uk/watch?v=abcdefghijk
	yget http://youtube.com/v/abcdefghijk
	yget http://www.youtube.com/view_play_list?p=abcdefghijklmnop
	yget http://youtube.com/p/abcdefghijklmnop

the script tries to get the H.264 encoded version (&fmt=18) first
